Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco, spoke with Turkish Interior Minister Efkan Ala to express condolences for the recent attack at Istanbul's Ataturk International Airport and offer U.S. support in combating terrorism. Monaco praised the bravery of Turkish security forces and Turkey's resilience in quickly reopening the airport. They agreed to continue counterterrorism cooperation and Monaco offered U.S. government support in investigating the attack and addressing the ongoing threat of terrorism.